  sodium: 1 g
  serving size: 550
time required: 30 minutes
---

Pour the @water{300%ml} into a large #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g}, a pinch of @salt{} and lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

> The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the @green beans{99%g} then chop into thirds. Chop the @whiting fillet{4} into roughly 3cm chunks.

While the rice cooks, heat a splash of @oil{} in another large saucepan over medium heat. When hot, add the red onion, stir and gently fry until softened stirring occasionally, ~{5%minutes}. Add the @north Indian style spice mix{1/2} and mix thoroughly. Cook for ~{1%minute} then pour in the @water{125%ml}. Bring to the boil and stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1/2}.

Lower the heat on the curry and add the chunks of whiting. Make sure they are at least partially submerged in the sauce. Cover the pan with a lid and simmer gently until the fish is cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> Do not stir the fish whilst it cooks, it's very fragile!

When the fish is almost cooked, carefully stir in the @crème fraîche{100%g} and heat until everything is piping hot, another ~{2%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> The fish is cooked when the centre is opaque.

While the fish cooks, heat a #frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil). Add the @desiccated coconut{12.5%g} and toast until golden, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn or toss frequently to make sure it doesn't burn. Transfer to a #bowl{} then return the pan to medium-high heat with a splash of @oil{}. When hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{} every now and then to help the beans steam. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and get ready to serve.

Fluff the rice up with a #fork{} and share between your bowls. Spoon the fish curry over and top with the green beans. Finish with a sprinkling of toasted coconut. Tuck in!